{"title":"Crust Bikes: Northbank Pedals","link":"https://theradavist.com/crust-bikes-northbank-pedals/","date":1705522074000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/CrustBikesNorthbankPedal.jpg?fit=1200,1365&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/CrustBikesNorthbankPedal.jpg?w=2048&amp;quality=75 2048w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/CrustBikesNorthbankPedal.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/CrustBikesNorthbankPedal.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/CrustBikesNorthbankPedal.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/CrustBikesNorthbankPedal.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><em>Always on the lookout for solid, metal pedals, the <a href=\"https://crustbikes.com/products/crust-pedal\" target=\"_blank\">Crust Bikes Northbak pedal</a> caught our eyes in the Latest &amp; Greatest section of their webshop…</em><span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/FP_3664.jpg?fit=1200,1365&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/FP_3664.jpg?w=2048&amp;quality=75 2048w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/FP_3664.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/FP_3664.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/FP_3664.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/FP_3664.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/FP_3649.jpg?fit=1200,1365&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/FP_3649.jpg?w=2048&amp;quality=75 2048w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/FP_3649.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/FP_3649.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/FP_3649.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/FP_3649.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>The <a href=\"https://crustbikes.com/products/crust-pedal\" target=\"_blank\">Northbank pedal</a> is named after one of the two main riverbank trails in Richmond, where Crust Bikes US is based. It’s a durable, low-profile pedal that looks good and won’t dent your wallet at $90. With enough bite to hold your feet planted in the rough stuff but the option to remove the replaceable pins to dial in your preferred grip.</p>\n<p>These are based on a medium-sized platform, hitting the middle ground of pedal platform size preferences. The CNC aluminum body spins on a steel spindle utilizing a sealed needle bearing and an LSL self-lubricating bushing.</p>\n<p><strong>Details:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Made in Taiwan</li>\n<li>CNC’d Aluminum</li>\n<li>Colors- Silver, Brown, Purple, or Splash</li>\n<li>Platform Size- 9.5cm L x 10.5cm W</li>\n<li>Thickness- 1.75cm at the spindle and 1.5cm at the ends</li>\n<li>Sealed Needle Bearing &amp; LSL Bushing</li>\n<li>Spindle Thread- 9/16″</li>\n<li>Weight (Per Pair)- 345g (12.15oz)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>See more at <a href=\"https://crustbikes.com/products/crust-pedal\" target=\"_blank\">Crust Bikes</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/crust-bikes-northbank-pedals/\">Crust Bikes: Northbank Pedals</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"99837dff6688b4fddee002af881cf2312ee393fe008026716c05616391493edf","category":"Cycling"}